description:
The program seeks to promote and institutionalize coconut-based enterprises through an integrated resource-service convergence approach to increase farm productivity and incomes of the small coconut farming communities.

The program has four (4) components, namely:
1) Coconut-Coffee Enterprise Development Project;
2) Coconut-Cacao-Based Enterprise Development Project;
3) Coconut Intercropping Project; and
4) Community/Household-level Coconut Processing Project.

Specifically, the program aims to: 
1. Encourage an integrated coconut-based enterprise by putting in place appropriate development support systems; 
2. Showcase coconut-based enterprise model through farm diversification and value-adding technologies managed by CBO or MSME as a tool for income and job generations;
3.  Improve and promote farmers' access to technology, production support services, information, credit and market; and
4. Harness capacities of CBOs and/or MSMEs and members including women, as entrepreneurs using coconut as the medium.

